      "side": 1,
      "message": "The core fix is correct and well-reasoned. The old code captured writeBus/writeAddr from globals after a D-Bus yield point,, where interleaving coroutines could corrupt them.\n\nThe new code snapshots bus/addr from deviceHashes before the yield and stores them in a per-device FruWriteCtx — this eliminates the race entirely.\n\nOne minor gap: writeTimerDevId is still a single global. If two devices have in-progress partial writes (neither has reached atEnd), the second device overwrites writeTimerDevId, and the first device\u0027s buffered data is never flushed by the timer.\n\nplease correct me if my understanding is wrong ?",
      "range": {
